I'll get you to your mother.

803
00:53:40,408 --> 00:53:41,908
She left a long time ago.

804
00:53:41,991 --> 00:53:44,116
-To your grandparents, then.
-They're dead.

805
00:53:44,200 --> 00:53:46,450
Uncles? Anything?

806
00:53:52,283 --> 00:53:54,575
[soft music plays]

807
00:53:56,075 --> 00:53:58,116
We'll figure it out, okay?

808
00:53:59,783 --> 00:54:00,783
Okay.

809
00:54:01,616 --> 00:54:04,200
So, here's
an unrelated question.

810
00:54:05,616 --> 00:54:06,908
Do you know how to drive?

811
00:54:08,325 --> 00:54:10,450
[Sam] Let's go over it
one more time. Left.

812
00:54:11,366 --> 00:54:12,408
[Sam] Right.

813
00:54:12,491 --> 00:54:14,075
Yes, I've got it already.

814
00:54:14,158 --> 00:54:16,408
"D" is for drive.
"R" is for reverse.

815
00:54:16,491 --> 00:54:19,658
And you get to do the easy part,
stepping on the gas and brakes.

816
00:54:20,325 --> 00:54:22,658
Don't be a smart-ass.
Turn the key.

817
00:54:22,741 --> 00:54:24,533
[engine revs]

818
00:54:24,616 --> 00:54:25,950
Put it in drive.

819
00:54:27,366 --> 00:54:28,575
Let's go.

820
00:54:32,450 --> 00:54:34,491
[suspenseful music]

821
00:54:48,241 --> 00:54:49,991
That's it. Straighten up.

822
00:54:51,950 --> 00:54:53,241
[laughs] I'm driving.

823
00:54:53,825 --> 00:54:54,908
Yes, you are.

824
00:54:54,991 --> 00:54:56,325
[tires screeching]

825
00:54:56,408 --> 00:54:58,158
[engines revving]

826
00:54:59,325 --> 00:55:01,033
[tires screeching]

827
00:55:03,450 --> 00:55:05,366
-Don't worry about the bullets.
-[guns cocking]

828
00:55:06,616 --> 00:55:07,908
Reverse. Now.

829
00:55:09,991 --> 00:55:12,408
-[engine revs]
-Hard left!

830
00:55:14,866 --> 00:55:16,491
-Put it in drive.
-Yeah.

831
00:55:17,366 --> 00:55:18,658
[tires screeching]

832
00:55:18,741 --> 00:55:20,075
-[Emily panting]
-That's it.

833
00:55:21,866 --> 00:55:23,325
-Hard left.
-[tires screech]

834
00:55:23,408 --> 00:55:24,908
-Go, go, go.
-[smashing]

835
00:55:26,783 --> 00:55:28,283
[rapid gunfire]

836
00:55:28,908 --> 00:55:29,741
[man] Damn it!

837
00:55:30,408 --> 00:55:31,991
[Sam] Get ready. Hard left.

838
00:55:33,700 --> 00:55:35,033
And another hard left.

839
00:55:36,825 --> 00:55:37,908
[tires screech]

840
00:55:39,450 --> 00:55:40,950
-[screeching of tires]
-Shh.

841
00:55:47,158 --> 00:55:48,533
[ominous music]

842
00:55:49,700 --> 00:55:52,241
[whispers] Okay.
Put it in reverse.

843
00:55:56,408 --> 00:55:58,783
-Hard right!
-[engine revving]

844
00:56:00,450 --> 00:56:01,825
[Sam] Put it in drive.

845
00:56:07,200 --> 00:56:08,491
Hard left.

846
00:56:09,325 --> 00:56:11,158
Put it in reverse.
[panting]

847
00:56:13,075 --> 00:56:15,283
-[tense music plays]
-Okay, kill the lights!

848
00:56:23,033 --> 00:56:25,366
[suspenseful music]

849
00:56:37,450 --> 00:56:39,616
[suspenseful music continues]

850
00:56:39,700 --> 00:56:41,950
[whispers] Okay, be quiet.
Duck down.

851
00:56:42,033 --> 00:56:43,908
That's it. Get down.

852
00:56:46,325 --> 00:56:47,325
[horn honks]

853
00:56:51,783 --> 00:56:53,658
[men shouting]

854
00:56:55,366 --> 00:56:58,200
[Sam whispers] Okay.
Put it in drive...

855
00:56:59,866 --> 00:57:01,075
and close your eyes.

856
00:57:02,491 --> 00:57:04,366
[rapid gunfire]

857
00:57:07,200 --> 00:57:08,741
[rapid gunfire]

858
00:57:11,366 --> 00:57:12,283
[both grunting]

859
00:57:15,200 --> 00:57:16,533
Keep her straight.

860
00:57:18,783 --> 00:57:20,783
[smashing]

861
00:57:21,991 --> 00:57:22,866
Keep it straight.

862
00:57:23,450 --> 00:57:24,575
[screaming]

863
00:57:25,325 --> 00:57:26,408
[grunts]

864
00:57:30,325 --> 00:57:31,825
Are your eyes still closed?

865
00:57:32,450 --> 00:57:33,741
-Yes.
-Good girl.

866
00:57:34,283 --> 00:57:35,575
Put it in reverse.

867
00:57:36,283 --> 00:57:37,825
[Emily breathes shallowly]

868
00:57:38,450 --> 00:57:39,741
[gasps]

869
00:57:41,908 --> 00:57:43,408
[engine revving]

870
00:57:49,866 --> 00:57:50,783
[grunts]

871
00:57:50,866 --> 00:57:52,991
[car clanks and rattles]

872
00:57:53,075 --> 00:57:54,825
-[engine revs]
-[tires screech]

873
00:58:02,283 --> 00:58:04,033
[Emily] Can I turn on
the radio?

874
00:58:04,950 --> 00:58:06,450
Go nuts.

875
00:58:08,241 --> 00:58:09,991
["French Disko"
by Stereolab plays]

876
00:58:10,075 --> 00:58:11,991
♪ Though this world's
essentially ♪

877
00:58:12,075 --> 00:58:15,116
♪ An absurd place
to be living in ♪

878
00:58:15,200 --> 00:58:19,825
♪ It doesn't call for
bubble withdrawal ♪

879
00:58:21,450 --> 00:58:24,658
♪ I've been told
it's a fact of life ♪

880
00:58:24,741 --> 00:58:26,075
[music fades out]

881
00:58:27,450 --> 00:58:29,200
[song resumes on radio]

882
00:58:29,741 --> 00:58:32,616
♪ Though this world's
essentially ♪

883
00:58:32,700 --> 00:58:36,075
♪ An absurd place
to be living in ♪

884
00:58:36,158 --> 00:58:39,908
♪ It doesn't call for
bubble withdrawal ♪

885
00:58:39,991 --> 00:58:41,325
[phone rings]

886
00:58:42,283 --> 00:58:43,450
[song ends abruptly]

887
00:58:58,658 --> 00:59:00,033
[suspenseful music plays]

888
00:59:04,116 --> 00:59:06,366
[Sam whispering]
Emily, doorbell.

889
00:59:08,825 --> 00:59:10,116
[doorbell rings]

890
00:59:21,700 --> 00:59:23,950
[music intensifies]

891
00:59:26,741 --> 00:59:27,825
[music stops abruptly]

892
00:59:28,741 --> 00:59:30,991
[woman] Didn't I teach you
to always guard your back?

893
00:59:36,950 --> 00:59:38,158
[gasps]

894
00:59:41,658 --> 00:59:43,033
[tremulously] Hi, Mom.

895
00:59:44,533 --> 00:59:45,616
[whispers] Hi.

896
00:59:47,741 --> 00:59:49,450
[soft emotional music]

897
00:59:55,283 --> 00:59:56,700
[whispers] Is this, um...

898
00:59:59,158 --> 01:00:00,116
Am I a grandmother?

899
01:00:01,325 --> 01:00:02,491
God, no.

900
01:00:03,908 --> 01:00:05,408
[sharp exhale]

901
01:00:06,200 --> 01:00:08,200
Hi. I'm Emily.

902
01:00:08,950 --> 01:00:11,158
-I'm her apprentice.
-What?

903
01:00:11,241 --> 01:00:12,325
Emily.

904
01:00:12,825 --> 01:00:14,033
Come.

905
01:00:14,616 --> 01:00:16,241
[sighs, sniffs]

906
01:00:22,866 --> 01:00:25,783
[on TV] ...the additional
burden of needing to care

907
01:00:25,866 --> 01:00:27,908
for her
twelve-month-old daughter.

908
01:00:27,991 --> 01:00:29,366
It will be at least a year...

909
01:00:30,075 --> 01:00:31,616
[electrical zapping]

910
01:00:36,158 --> 01:00:38,533
That is a hell of a story.

911
01:00:40,033 --> 01:00:41,825
Mm. Hell of a night.

912
01:00:44,116 --> 01:00:46,575
Um...
Try wiggling your fingers.

913
01:00:47,241 --> 01:00:50,033
-Feeling should come back in no time.
-Yeah, it's already working.

914
01:00:50,116 --> 01:00:51,491
Excellent.

915
01:00:55,616 --> 01:00:57,741
You look really good.
Are you eating well?

916
01:00:57,825 --> 01:00:58,991
Cut the crap, Ma.

917
01:01:00,825 --> 01:01:02,908
Where have you been
for the last 15 years?

918
01:01:04,200 --> 01:01:05,283
Around.

919
01:01:08,575 --> 01:01:09,700
Watching you.

920
01:01:12,241 --> 01:01:13,866
Making sure you're safe.

921
01:01:14,533 --> 01:01:15,825
Great parenting.

922
01:01:16,450 --> 01:01:18,658
Glad to see you taking
an interest in my career.

923
01:01:18,741 --> 01:01:21,991
-I never wanted this life for you.
-How's that working out for you?

924
01:01:26,908 --> 01:01:30,116
I wanted to stay with you
and your aunts, but I couldn't.

925
01:01:30,866 --> 01:01:32,116
Why not?

926
01:01:35,075 --> 01:01:36,366
Because I fucked up.

927
01:01:42,325 --> 01:01:43,658
[quietly] I fucked up.

928
01:01:45,658 --> 01:01:47,325
I was young when I had you.

929
01:01:47,408 --> 01:01:48,616
[soft emotional music]

930
01:01:49,241 --> 01:01:51,866
We left London, followed your
father here. When he died--

931
01:01:51,950 --> 01:01:53,741
When he was murdered.

932
01:01:56,116 --> 01:01:58,908
When he was murdered,
you were a baby. I had nothing.

933
01:01:59,991 --> 01:02:01,616
No money, nowhere to go.

934
01:02:02,658 --> 01:02:04,658
I knew Anna May
from your dad's work.

935
01:02:06,241 --> 01:02:08,450
She and the other aunts
took us in.

936
01:02:09,616 --> 01:02:11,491
The best years of my life.

937
01:02:11,575 --> 01:02:13,075
Me too.

938
01:02:16,908 --> 01:02:20,200
Fast-forward twelve years,
and I find out who shot your dad.

939
01:02:21,783 --> 01:02:23,075
The Russians?

940
01:02:23,908 --> 01:02:25,616
The Russians from the diner?

941
01:02:26,158 --> 01:02:29,575
Once I knew, I couldn't let him
walk around enjoying life...

942
01:02:31,408 --> 01:02:32,950
knowing what he did to us.

943
01:02:35,116 --> 01:02:38,616
But he was in bed with The Firm,
so there was a price to pay.

944
01:02:40,075 --> 01:02:42,450
Once I killed him,
there was a mark on my back.

945
01:02:44,866 --> 01:02:46,533
[soft emotional music]

946
01:02:49,491 --> 01:02:51,950
[voice breaks]
I couldn't take you with me.

947
01:02:54,408 --> 01:02:55,908
I couldn't risk your life.

948
01:02:59,408 --> 01:03:01,658
So I made Nathan promise
to keep you safe.

949
01:03:05,950 --> 01:03:07,325
I guess that's over.

950
01:03:10,616 --> 01:03:14,116
There isn't a day that goes by
I don't regret pulling that trigger.

951
01:03:14,616 --> 01:03:16,825
But back then,
I couldn't help myself.

952
01:03:21,408 --> 01:03:22,658
I'm sorry.

953
01:03:26,033 --> 01:03:27,825
[music fades out]

954
01:03:35,241 --> 01:03:37,533
Does the kid know
about you and her dad?

955
01:03:37,616 --> 01:03:38,616
[Sam] No.

956
01:03:41,033 --> 01:03:42,366
But she's smart.

957
01:03:43,700 --> 01:03:44,866
She'll figure it out.

958
01:03:45,825 --> 01:03:47,325
What happens when she does?

959
01:03:55,825 --> 01:03:58,491
-[inaudible TV chatter]
-[soft emotional music]

960
01:04:04,616 --> 01:04:06,575
I think
there's a bad man outside.

961
01:04:12,575 --> 01:04:13,908
We have to get out of here.

962
01:04:18,991 --> 01:04:21,783
-So, what's the plan?
-Can you press the lobby button?

963
01:04:21,866 --> 01:04:24,325
-What plan?
-Come on, you always have a plan.

964
01:04:24,408 --> 01:04:27,033
A secret escape route?
A warehouse filled with guns?

965
01:04:27,116 --> 01:04:28,158
I called us an Uber.

966
01:04:28,241 --> 01:04:29,700
-Are you kidding me?
-No.

967
01:04:29,783 --> 01:04:31,908
An Uber. What the hell
are you talking about?

968
01:04:31,991 --> 01:04:33,741
I know you. You make plans.

969
01:04:33,825 --> 01:04:35,991
And then you make plans
to make other plans.

970
01:04:36,075 --> 01:04:39,075
-You're frothing at the mouth.
-[rousing music]

971
01:04:39,158 --> 01:04:40,658
-It's unbecoming.
-[Sam scoffs]

972
01:04:47,033 --> 01:04:48,241
[elevator dings]

973
01:04:49,366 --> 01:04:51,283
[dramatic music]

974
01:04:59,408 --> 01:05:00,450
[whimpers]

975
01:05:01,533 --> 01:05:02,908
[screams] Get them!

976
01:05:02,991 --> 01:05:04,491
[men clamouring]

977
01:05:06,116 --> 01:05:08,283
[music intensifies]

978
01:05:08,366 --> 01:05:09,741
[mockingly] Don't feel bad.

979
01:05:10,241 --> 01:05:11,741
Could happen to anyone.

980
01:05:11,825 --> 01:05:13,533
My hand is still paralyzed.

981
01:05:13,616 --> 01:05:15,158
Yeah, course it is.

982
01:05:15,241 --> 01:05:17,075
-It is.
-I know.

983
01:05:17,158 --> 01:05:17,991
[elevator dings]

984
01:05:26,033 --> 01:05:27,825
[tense music]

985
01:05:28,700 --> 01:05:30,658
[Scarlet] Right.
After you, ladies.

986
01:05:31,408 --> 01:05:33,241
[Scarlet] Come on. Hurry up.

987
01:05:33,908 --> 01:05:35,908
-[Sam] Where does it go?
-Fucking Narnia.

988
01:05:35,991 --> 01:05:36,991
Go. In.

989
01:05:37,491 --> 01:05:39,158
-In!
-[scoffs] Fine.

990
01:05:52,116 --> 01:05:55,158
-[Sam] No plan, huh?
-[Scarlet] Now is not the time.

991
01:05:56,116 --> 01:05:57,366
Out of my way.

992
01:06:01,700 --> 01:06:02,825
[echoing boom]

993
01:06:02,908 --> 01:06:05,116
-[Sam] Need help, Ma?
-No, thank you.

994
01:06:05,200 --> 01:06:06,408
I'm quite capable...

995
01:06:07,200 --> 01:06:10,200
of disposing of one...
[grunts]

996
01:06:10,283 --> 01:06:11,366
...idiotic grate.

997
01:06:21,366 --> 01:06:22,825
[hatch creaking]

998
01:06:25,658 --> 01:06:27,783
[suspenseful music]

999
01:06:37,616 --> 01:06:41,408
["Poupée de Cire, Poupée de Son"
by France Gall plays quietly]

1000
01:06:41,491 --> 01:06:42,533
[banging]

1001
01:06:42,616 --> 01:06:44,158
[clattering]

1002
01:06:47,741 --> 01:06:51,200
[breathless] That freezer is a mess.
It's completely unacceptable.

1003
01:06:54,366 --> 01:06:56,325
[dramatic music]

1004
01:07:01,366 --> 01:07:03,533
-Come on.
-Are you kidding me?

1005
01:07:04,075 --> 01:07:05,825
-We have to go.
-Go where?

1006
01:07:05,908 --> 01:07:07,825
Obviously your plan
was to end up here.

1007
01:07:07,908 --> 01:07:09,908
-That was a long time ago.
-Mom...

1008
01:07:10,658 --> 01:07:12,616
-I'm not going in there.
-Mom, listen.

1009
01:07:12,700 --> 01:07:15,116
We need weapons and a car.
We need a safe house!

1010
01:07:15,200 --> 01:07:17,491
I'm not sure they'd let me in!

1011
01:07:17,575 --> 01:07:19,241
Only one way to find out.

1012
01:07:20,658 --> 01:07:22,783
-[dramatic music]
-[church bells chiming]

1013
01:07:28,950 --> 01:07:30,075
Hey.

1014
01:07:45,241 --> 01:07:47,825
For the record, I still think
this is a shit idea.

1015
01:07:51,241 --> 01:07:52,825
[dramatic music plays]

1016
01:07:57,866 --> 01:07:59,741
[music fades out]

1017
01:08:01,450 --> 01:08:02,658
Madeleine?

1018
01:08:05,241 --> 01:08:07,033
-[Sam sighs]
-[gun cocking]

1019
01:08:08,991 --> 01:08:11,991
[Anna May] Girls,
I think I see a ghost.

1020
01:08:16,908 --> 01:08:19,241
-Hi, Madeleine.
-Hi, Scarlet.

1021
01:08:19,325 --> 01:08:20,491
[Scarlet] Florence.

1022
01:08:22,950 --> 01:08:24,658
-Hi, Anna May.
-No.

1023
01:08:25,325 --> 01:08:27,366
No, no. You don't get to talk.

1024
01:08:28,491 --> 01:08:31,158
Because you're a ghost,
and ghosts can't talk.

1025
01:08:31,658 --> 01:08:32,908
You know how I know that?

1026
01:08:33,491 --> 01:08:34,866
Can we do this later?

1027
01:08:34,950 --> 01:08:36,491
Because if ghosts could talk,

1028
01:08:37,366 --> 01:08:40,075
they would say something
before disappearing.

1029
01:08:40,158 --> 01:08:43,283
Or at least leave a note.
But they can't.

1030
01:08:43,366 --> 01:08:46,033
So, ipso facto,
you're a ghost.

1031
01:08:46,866 --> 01:08:48,450
-I'm sorry.
-[shouts] Fuck you.

1032
01:08:48,533 --> 01:08:50,866
Language, Anna May.
There's a child present.

1033
01:08:50,950 --> 01:08:52,241
Fine.

1034
01:08:53,241 --> 01:08:55,783
-Fudge you.
-Fudge you.

1035
01:08:55,866 --> 01:08:57,825
-Fudge you!
-[giggles]

1036
01:08:59,991 --> 01:09:01,866
-[ominous music]
-[Emily giggles]

1037
01:09:01,950 --> 01:09:05,116
And why is there a toddler
in our place of business?

1038
01:09:06,908 --> 01:09:07,908
The short version?

1039
01:09:08,700 --> 01:09:09,658
Please.

1040
01:09:10,325 --> 01:09:13,200
Her father was killed
and she has nowhere else to go.

1041
01:09:13,283 --> 01:09:14,908
I was downsized by The Firm,

1042
01:09:14,991 --> 01:09:18,283
and they fed me to McAlester's
endless supply of thugs.

1043
01:09:18,366 --> 01:09:19,991
And you decided to come here?

1044
01:09:20,075 --> 01:09:21,908
Shall we return
at a more convenient time?

1045
01:09:22,491 --> 01:09:23,741
Maybe you should.

1046
01:09:23,825 --> 01:09:26,200
[Anna May] It seems like
whenever you come here,

1047
01:09:26,283 --> 01:09:27,908
you bring a war with you.

1048
01:09:30,200 --> 01:09:31,325
Bring your problems--

1049
01:09:32,950 --> 01:09:34,325
We need to table this for now.

1050
01:09:34,408 --> 01:09:36,200
[loud bang at door]

1051
01:09:38,075 --> 01:09:39,241
Seconded.

1052
01:09:39,783 --> 01:09:40,950
Let's go down.

1053
01:09:45,908 --> 01:09:47,825
[multiple phones ringing]

1054
01:09:49,408 --> 01:09:52,533
[phones ringing]

1055
01:09:53,533 --> 01:09:55,116
[suspenseful music]

1056
01:09:56,866 --> 01:09:58,200
[loud, resonant bang]

1057
01:09:59,116 --> 01:10:00,491
Go and take Emily.

1058
01:10:00,991 --> 01:10:02,491
I'll buy us some time.

1059
01:10:04,700 --> 01:10:07,241
-I think I should stay.
-[banging]

1060
01:10:09,533 --> 01:10:10,658
No.

1061
01:10:11,241 --> 01:10:12,741
I screwed this up.

